2.  Synopsys Commands                                        Command Reference
                             report_track_patterns

NAME
       report_track_patterns
              Reports  track  patterns  for  specified routing layers and site
              definitions.

SYNTAX
       int report_track_patterns
              -layers layer_list
              [-sites site_def_list]
              [-tech tech]
              [-library library]
              [-verbose]
              [-nosplit]
              [-significant_digits digits]

   Data Types
       layer_list     string
       site_def_list  list
       tech           collection
       library        string or collection
       digits         int

ARGUMENTS
       -layers layer_list
              Specifies the routing layers from which to report the track pat-
              tern.  Specify the layers by using a collection or by specifying
              a list of layer names from the technology.

       -sites site_def_list
              Specifies the site definitions from which to  report  the  track
              pattern.   Specify  the site definition by using a collection or
              by specifying a list of site definition names from the  technol-
              ogy.   If  not specified, the default site definition is used if
              available, otherwise an error is issued.

       -tech tech
              Track pattern will be reported from this technology.  Default is
              the  current  library's tech.  This option is mutually exclusive
              with the -library option.

       -library library
              Track pattern will be  reported  from  the  technology  of  this
              library.   Default is the current library.  This option is mutu-
              ally exclusive with the -tech option.

       -verbose
              There is no effect using this option right now. In  the  future,
              it  may  report  additional  columns of data when this option is
              specified.

       -nosplit
              Does not split lines if column overflows.

       -significant_digits digits
              Specifies the number of digits to the right of the decimal point
              that are to be reported. Allowed values are 0-13; the default is
              determined by  the  report_default_significant_digits  variable,
              whose  default  value is 2. Use this option if you want to over-
              ride the default.

DESCRIPTION
       This command displays information about the track patterns in  a  tech-
       nology.

EXAMPLES
       The  following  example reports all track patterns in the technology of
       the current library.

         prompt> report_track_patterns
         Site_def  Layer  Type         Direction   Spacing Offset  Width   Reserved  Mask
         --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
         unit      M1     non_uniform  vertical    --      0.30    0.15    true      mask_one
         unit      M1     non_uniform  vertical    --      0.50    0.10    false     mask_two
         unit      M1     non_uniform  vertical    --      0.70    0.10    true      mask_one
         unit      M1     non_uniform  vertical    --      1.05    0.10    false     mask_two
         unit      M2     non_uniform  horizontal  --      0.10    0.10    false     mask_one
         unit      M2     non_uniform  horizontal  --      0.25    0.15    true      mask_two
         unit      M3     uniform      vertical    0.20    0.30    0.10    false     mask_one mask_two
         unit      M4     uniform      horizontal  0.20    0.10    0.10    false     mask_two mask_one
         unit      M5     uniform      horizontal  0.14    0.07    --      --        --
         unit      M6     uniform      horizontal  0.14    0.07    --      --        --
         1

SEE ALSO
       create_track_pattern(2)
       remove_track_patterns(2)

